---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Online PhD | Brenkley Doctoral College" description="Brenkley Doctoral College's fully online PhD — 3 to 6 years, maximum flexibility, expert supervision. The doctorate designed around your life. £6,500 per year.">

  <section class="bg-surface border-b border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">Programme</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Online PhD</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-accent font-medium mb-4">PhD &mdash; 3 to 6 years &mdash; £6,500 per year &mdash; Fully Online</p>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl">Brenkley Doctoral College's Online PhD offers the full intellectual rigour of a traditional doctorate with none of the residential constraints. Study is entirely online, supervision is conducted remotely, and your pace is flexible within a structured framework. Built for professionals who cannot sacrifice flexibility without sacrificing quality.</p>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl mt-4">Year 1 is delivered by Brenkley Doctoral College as the <a href="/programmes/mphil/" class="text-accent underline">Extended Advanced Diploma</a> (SCQF Level 11, 180 credits), including an applied internship. Years 2 and 3 are completed at a partner university of your choice, subject to that university's own admissions and articulation process.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">3–6 Years</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Flexible pace — you choose slow or standard track</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">£6,500/yr</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Year 1, billed annually. Years 2–3 fees are set by your chosen partner university.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">Fully Online</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">No residential requirement. Study anywhere in the world.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">Any Sector</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Open to any professional background — business, public, healthcare, education</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Flexibility</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Study On Your Terms</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">The Online PhD at Brenkley Doctoral College is designed for researchers who need maximum flexibility. All learning is asynchronous — there are no fixed lecture times. Live supervision meetings are scheduled at mutually convenient times, including evenings and weekends where needed. Residential attendance is optional, not mandatory.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">You choose between a standard three-year track and an extended track of up to six years. The extended track is ideal for professionals whose work responsibilities make standard pace impractical. Both tracks meet the same academic standards and award the same qualification.</p>
          <p class="text-muted">The Online PhD is our most internationally accessible programme. We have supervised researchers in the UK, Europe, the Middle East, East Africa, and Southeast Asia. Time zone differences are accommodated in supervision scheduling.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Rigour</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">No Compromise on Quality</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">Flexibility does not mean lower standards. The Online PhD at Brenkley Doctoral College is a full doctoral degree, requiring an original and significant contribution to knowledge in your field. The thesis is examined by an independent external examiner and an internal examiner in a viva voce examination.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">All the academic support structures that apply to our residential programmes apply equally to Online PhD researchers — supervision logging, annual review milestones, methods training, library access, and peer community.</p>
          <div class="card mt-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-muted"><strong class="text-foreground">Same qualification:</strong> The Online PhD is examined to the same standard as any other Brenkley Doctoral College doctoral award. There is no distinction on your qualification certificate between online and residential study.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Structure -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-y border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Structure</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Flexible But Structured</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">The Online PhD is structured around three broad phases, each with clear milestones. Flexible pace means you can move through phases faster or slower than standard — within agreed parameters and with supervisor support. Phase 1 is delivered by Brenkley Doctoral College; Phases 2 and 3 are completed at the partner university you progress to.</p>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">The Phase 1 internship can be hosted by your own employer if you are already working, or arranged through our employer network if you need a placement — see <a href="/programmes/mphil/#internship" class="text-accent underline">how the internship works</a>.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3 text-accent">Phase 1: Foundation</h3>
          <p class="text-xs font-medium text-muted uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">Delivered by Brenkley Doctoral College</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium mb-3">Months 1–12 (standard) / Months 1–18 (extended)</p>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Research paradigms and philosophical foundations</li>
            <li>Research design for your specific topic</li>
            <li>Literature review development</li>
            <li>Research proposal approval</li>
            <li>Ethics application and approval</li>
            <li>Applied internship — theory into practice</li>
            <li>Annual Review 1</li>
            <li>Award of Extended Advanced Diploma (SCQF 11, 180 credits)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3 text-accent">Phase 2: Inquiry</h3>
          <p class="text-xs font-medium text-muted uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">Delivered by your chosen partner university</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium mb-3">Months 13–24 (standard) / Months 19–36 (extended)</p>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Admission via the partner university's articulation process</li>
            <li>Advanced methods training (online modules)</li>
            <li>Data collection in professional context</li>
            <li>Data analysis and emerging findings</li>
            <li>Peer research seminar presentation</li>
            <li>Annual Review 2</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3 text-accent">Phase 3: Completion</h3>
          <p class="text-xs font-medium text-muted uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">Delivered by your chosen partner university</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium mb-3">Months 25–36 (standard) / Months 37–72 (extended)</p>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Thesis writing with supervisor feedback cycles</li>
            <li>Academic writing support module</li>
            <li>Pre-submission panel review</li>
            <li>Thesis submission</li>
            <li>Viva voce examination</li>
            <li>Award of PhD by the partner university</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Progression -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-t border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Progression</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">You Choose Your Partner University</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8 max-w-3xl">On successful completion of Year 1, you choose which partner university you progress to for Years 2 and 3, rather than being assigned one. Brenkley Doctoral College maintains progression arrangements with a network of partner universities; final admission is confirmed through each university's own admissions and articulation process, not guaranteed automatically.</p>
      <div class="card max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-muted"><strong class="text-foreground">No obligation to progress:</strong> Year 1 stands on its own as the Extended Advanced Diploma — a complete, SCQF-rated qualification with an applied internship. Progression to Years 2–3 is optional and by choice.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Entry Requirements</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Who Can Apply</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Academic</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Master's degree at Merit or Distinction in a relevant subject, or equivalent Level 7 professional qualification. Strong undergraduate performance in the absence of a Master's may be considered alongside professional experience.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Professional</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Significant professional experience in a relevant field. The Online PhD is appropriate for professionals across all sectors — the key requirement is that you have a context in which to conduct your research.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Research Proposal</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">A preliminary research proposal of 1,500–2,000 words. The proposal is reviewed by the Academic Lead for Research &amp; Enterprise and a potential supervisor to assess topic viability and supervisory fit.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">English Language</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">For international applicants whose first language is not English: IELTS 6.5 overall with no component below 6.0, or equivalent recognised qualification.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-surface border-t border-border py-16 px-6 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Your research, your pace</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">The Online PhD was built for people who cannot wait for their professional life to be less busy before they start their doctorate. Apply now, and study around the life you already have.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
        <a href="/apply" class="btn-primary">Apply now</a>
        <a href="/connect" class="btn-outline">Ask us anything</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
